americas 36th state with a presidential primary setting up hopes 
for a regional set of primaries that would attract candidates to 
the pacific northwest 
the senate voted 38 to 10 for an initiative submitted by the 
people after the legislature had balked for years at the idea of 
eliminating the states muchmaligned caucus system of choosing 
national convention delegates 
as drafted the legislation would enable washington to join 
oregon idaho and montana on the date oregon uses the fourth 
tuesday in may 
