quick movement is nearly unprecedented for a major piece of 
legislation dealing with the financial system and the host of 
special interest groups representing its segments but this time 
fear is a driving force 
sampl depositors are withdrawing their funds in record amounts 
35 billion from november through february and members of 
congress are afraid to risk further deterioration 
sampl regulators at the federal home loan bank board say the huge 
withdrawals are not abnormal when interest rates rise and mutual 
funds and other competitors offer investors a better return 
