from 1200 to the dollar 
the government uses the exchange rate to pay exporters and to 
finance imports of vital drugs and food staples the floating free 
market rate which registered 1550 intis to the dollar saturday 
is used for nearly all other transactions 
by devaluing the inti the government hopes to spur exports and 
reduce a growing trade deficit the devaluation also is aimed at 
cutting the deficit by reducing the amount the government pays to 
subsidize imports 
