franklin a korn a bell telephone 
laboratories researcher who helped create touchtone telephones and 
the directdial longdistance system has died at the age of 83 
korn who retired from bell labs in 1970 after 50 years with the 
company died at home friday of kidney failure said his daughter 
barbara trimmer hudyk 
korn was director of telephone laboratories at the former 
western electric plant here now owned by atampt he was credited with 
developing a nationwide directdial military telephone network 
during world war ii and with the development of touchtone dialing 
he also coinvented the switching system used by telephone 
companies until the mid1970s when electronic switching was 
introduced according to harold heckendorn retired engineering 
manager of the western electric plant 
korn held about 15 telephonerelated patents said his grandson 
david trimmer and was named a fellow of the institute of 
electronic and electrical engineers the highest honor bestowed by 
the professional organization 
he is survived by his wife a daughter two grandchildren and a 
greatgrandchild family members said 
